. * Sign Test on how often a positive value and how often a negative value was assigned by each subject:
. 
. * Indicator for positive intrinsic value:
. gen pos=.
{txt}(690 missing values generated)

{com}. replace pos=1 if IV>0 & mae!=1
{txt}(409 real changes made)

{com}. * Number of assigned positive intrinsic values by subject:
. egen poscount=count(pos), by(subject)
{txt}
{com}. 
. * Indicator for negative intrinsic value:
. gen neg=.
{txt}(690 missing values generated)

{com}. replace neg=1 if IV<0
{txt}(159 real changes made)

{com}. replace neg=1 if mae==1
{txt}(72 real changes made)

{com}. * Number of assigned negative intrinsic values by subject:
. egen negcount=count(neg), by(subject)
{txt}
{com}. 
. * Signtest whether number if positive and negative intrinsic value assignments are equal:
. signtest poscount=negcount if situation==1

{txt}Sign test

        sign {c |}    observed    expected
{hline 13}{c +}{hline 24}
    positive {c |}{res}{col 17}        49{col 29}      31.5
    {txt}negative {c |}{res}{col 17}        14{col 29}      31.5
        {txt}zero {c |}{res}{col 17}         6{col 29}         6
{txt}{hline 13}{c +}{hline 24}
         all {c |}{res}{col 17}        69{col 29}        69

{txt}One-sided tests:
  Ho: median of poscount - negcount  = 0 vs.
  Ha: median of poscount - negcount  > 0
      Pr(#positive >= {res}49{txt}) =
         Binomial(n = {res}63{txt}, x >= {res}49{txt}, p = 0.5) = {res} 0.0000

{txt}  Ho: median of poscount - negcount  = 0 vs.
  Ha: median of poscount - negcount  < 0
      Pr(#negative >= {res}14{txt}) =
         Binomial(n = {res}63{txt}, x >= {res}14{txt}, p = 0.5) = {res} 1.0000

{txt}Two-sided test:
  Ho: median of poscount - negcount  = 0 vs.
  Ha: median of poscount - negcount  != 0
      Pr(#positive >= {res}49{txt} or #negative >= {res}49{txt}) =
         min(1, 2*Binomial(n = {res}63{txt}, x >= {res}49{txt}, p = 0.5)) = {res} 0.0000
{txt}
{com}. * 49 subjects assign a positive value more often.
. * 14 assign a negative value more often
. * 6 assign an equal number of positive and negative values.
. * Sign Test is significant at the p>0.001 level.
. 
